‚†Ä‚†Ä
I spent so many years as a teenager chasing trends that I was too slow to catch. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
The day I stopped with ultra-endurance events and decided I wanted to try feeling strong was the day that the way I looked at my body finally changed. It made me patient. There was no more pressure from feeling behind because my goal wasn‚Äôt visible to anyone else any more. It was just for me. ‚†Ä

I‚Äôve felt every kind of feeling about my body, and there‚Äôs nothing like feeling powerful üíõ

üî• Cable machine front squat (4 x 14): this variation unlocks the amazing benefits of a front squat but is super accessible and doesn‚Äôt take a barbell üôè ‚†Ä

I travelled across the country for a boy that didn‚Äôt care about me and cried the whole journey home when I was 17. I landed on my face when I was learning to backflip, and I was told I‚Äôm careless for giving up a PhD people (and the old me) would kill for to go after something unproven üôã‚Äç‚ôÄ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
But I know that if I don‚Äôt take something, nobody‚Äôs about to gift it to me just because I want it. I remind myself that either I look out for myself or nobody else will every time I feel scared. So if it‚Äôs that workout you wish you‚Äôd try, or the guy you‚Äôre hoping is going to come and say hi this time, or the job you wish you had. They‚Äôre all scary, but the world‚Äôs not going to magic them into existence ‚ú® ‚†Ä

HIIT day! 15 minutes and your bodyweight is all you need to start the week real good üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
I stuck to my classic circuit with 30s of work + 30s of rest before moving onto the next exercise, and hit three full rounds of the circuit for a 14min 30sec workout (who‚Äôs counting thoughüôã‚Äç‚ôÄ) ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
The benefits of HIIT really come from putting out a lot of energy when we‚Äôre working (which isn‚Äôt the same as just being tired) so don‚Äôt go cutting those rest periods üíõ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíæ Save and we can sweat whenever you need! üí¶ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Tuck jump to drop squat: our hips are bringing the knees up high in the tuck jump, and we‚Äôre landing back down softly on the balls of the feet. If you need a little more time to reset, you can always switch to two fast drop squats between each tuck jump üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Down dog with knee drive: extend the working leg niiiiice and high and tighten the abs as you drive it back in ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Side bound and back: these side bounds are in sets of two. We‚Äôre absorbing the first bound and changing direction as quickly as possible‚ö° I stick to one side each round and swap sides the next round ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Side-to-side shuffles: two shuffles per direction is perfect and means we‚Äôre changing directions and touching down often enough üî• ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Reverse plank marches: keep those hips nice and high, and try the easier variation (keep watching) if you prefer ‚ú® ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üéâü•≥üçæü•Ç Finished! ‚†Ä

Strong legs? Hi yes please üôã‚Äç‚ôÄ‚ò∫ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
I keep one varied lower body session like this every week üôè This balances out my other legs session where I go more for strength starting with squat or deadlift sets in the 1-5 rep range ü•≥ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Save this little puppy and let‚Äôs build some well rounded legs ü¶µüòú ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üî• Lunge into step up and knee drive (3 x 8 per side): flow from the lunge straight into the step up and keeping it as one continuous motion üí¶ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üî• Alternating side lunges (3 x 14 total): slightly rotating the foot positioning between each rep so the knee is in line with the foot on the working leg ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üî• Drop squats (4 x 10): we‚Äôre quickly lowering down into the squat position and popping right back up and bringing the legs back in ‚ò∫ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üî• KB lunge to knee drive and hold (3 x 12 total): an asymmetric load (the weight more to one side) is amazing for engaging all kinds of stabiliser muscles ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üî• KB rack open leg lunge (3 x 14 total): you can switch to holding dumbbells down by your side if you prefer. The focus is putting most of the weight through the front leg and just using the back foot for balance üòò ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
That‚Äôs the core of my leg workout finished üéâ Feel free to add in an extra move to tailor it to a particular goal you‚Äôre working on (I ended with 15 minutes of stretching) and you‚Äôre amazing üòç ‚†Ä

A fullllll upper body and core workout that‚Äôll engage so many muscles! üí™üî• ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
My upper body workouts are usually gymnastics based, but when I‚Äôm in the gym these 8 exercises hitting the shoulders, core, upper back, arms and chest are exactly the kind of work I do to feel strong across my whole upper body üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíæ Save for when you want to workout your whole upper body in one go! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Side-to-side press ups (3 x 12): the modification of going on your knees is a perfect variation for making these accessible while keeping the movement the same ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Rack pulls (4 x 6): rack pulls are a really incredible movement that made my squatting so much more powerful. The shoulders stay engaged and high without losing tension throughout and the back stays arched and you‚Äôre doing great ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Seated chin ups (3 x 10): your feet provide the assistance if you need it! Bending your knees and keeping the feet closer makes things easier, and you can straighten the knees as you build more of that muscle! üíÅ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Rotating bear taps (3 x 8): in the bear crawl position, we‚Äôre pivoting on the ball of the foot and keeping that core and planted shoulder engaged through the twist üíÉ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Half kneeling dumbbell press (3 x 10 per side): I prefer to do a lot of overhead movements in a seated or half kneeling position when I‚Äôm targeting my upper body to make sure there‚Äôs no assistance coming from down below ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Weighted hyperextensions (3 x 10): pulling the plate close to the chest is a great start, and overhead will engage a lot more of the shoulders too üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Straight arm plank reaches (3 x 14 total reps): holding up for the count of 2 at full extension for each rep is going to burn but going to work wonders for your core so I really recommend ‚ò∫Ô∏è ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí™ Side plank extension to close (3 x 10 per side): really keeping the hips high and facing forwards instead of rotating to the sky is super important! If this feels a little tough, go down onto the knee of the planted leg instead of the foot and you can build that strength! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Happy upper body day! Enjoy the strong feeling ‚ö°Ô∏èüôå

A sweattyyyy HIIT workout! üí¶üí¶ Just your bodyweight and 20 minutes is all we need for an amazing workout üî• ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
This one is a serious burner so I structured it a little differently to normal: still 30s on, then 30s rest before switching to the next move, but after the fifth exercise I rested for a full 60s (30s extra) before starting the next circuit to make sure these intervals really were high intensity üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Save for a sweat session you can do anywhere! üòò ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Squats with knee up: we‚Äôre squatting through the heels but coming onto the ball of the standing foot for the knee up ‚úå ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Squat thrust kneel-to-squat: keep the chest and chin up during the kneel as much as you can ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Pause squat jumps: a 2s hold is perfect, and jump nice and high landing softly on the balls of your feet ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Elevated knee touches: the elbow comes parallel to the knee so the forearm is just swiping the shin üí™ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Low alternating lunges: the lower the more intense üî• just push through the last 30s before a nice 60s rest and going again! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
I went for 4 rounds which took me just over 20 minutes and that was me done for the day! üòÖ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
For lots more super effective HIIT workouts, my training guide HIIT. (available in app form and packed with videos) has 40 unique sessions to get you sweating in under 25 minutes with over 100 amazing exercises and is available in the link in my bio now! ‚ö°

üî• Leg dayyyyy! üòçüí¶ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
These six moves are super accessible and will work beautifully together to build some strong legs fit for all kinds of working out üôå ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Nothing is a superset as I prioritise rest and form instead of volume for enabling strong, functional movement ‚úå ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Hit SAVE üíæ and let‚Äôs get stronger my friends! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Lateral transfers to curtsy lunge (3 x 14 total): stay low and slow throughout and control this exercise, really focusing on the weight shift from one side to the other. You can keep the plate at your chest if you prefer ‚ò∫ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Skier swing into lunge (3 x 14 total): the skier swing is mostly a drive with the glute with the knees juuust flexing slightly instead of a big bend at the knees which is a common mistake on KB swings üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Sumo Deadlifts (3 x 8): we‚Äôre pointing the feet, knees and quads slightly outwards, with a slightly wider leg stance than usual. Sumos should be putting less strain through the lower back which can be a useful variation for some people, but either way they‚Äôre an amazing compound move for getting real strong. If you‚Äôre new to sumos, I‚Äôd suggest putting them to the start so you can nail the technique üí™ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶ Goblet squat jumps (4 x 10): straight after that slow, strong exercise we‚Äôre following up with some explosiveness ‚ö° Keep that lower back engaged throughout and don‚Äôt drop the shoulders and you‚Äôre great ‚ù§ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üí¶  Box knee drive (3 x 8 per side): this last move is really working wonders ‚ú® for power through that whole leg so go hard and you‚Äôre finished! üôè

We were sharing an electric scooter through the city during the sunset and Mario suddenly slammed the brakes (nearly causing his second accident of the trip but I don‚Äôt need to be bringing that up ‚úåüôÉ) and told me to stand in front of this amazing reflection üåá He literally took two photos, walked back to the scooter and said you‚Äôre going to want to upload them. And here we are üòÇ

My super compound, functional workout yesterday was everything I needed ‚ö°Ô∏èüåº ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
First we hit legs while keeping the core and upper body engaged, and then go for a little upper bod too ‚Äòcause it‚Äôs a party and everyone‚Äôs invited üíÉüíå ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Save for when you next want to activate everything and feel real strong üî• ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ Plate ground to overhead (3 x 10): we‚Äôre driving through the quads and glutes and keeping the lower back tight throughout. Keep watching for a variation you can advance to if you‚Äôre feeling strong üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ KB lunge rotations (3 x 14 total): the rotation will ask your core to get involved and will create an asymmetric load meaning stabilising work through that lower body too üçë ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ Duck walks (4 x 12 paces): here we‚Äôre staying low and not bouncing, with most of the weight going through that front quad. Keep watching for an overhead variation you can advance to once you‚Äôre a pro üí™ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ Overhead lateral raises (3 x 14): I like to do these with my palms facing forward and straight arms for real engagement in my shoulders ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ Front squats (3 x 8): I love front squats so much for targeting my quads. If you‚Äôre still new to front squats, I‚Äôd recommend pulling them up toward the start of the workout ‚ò∫Ô∏è ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ Seated / assisted / full pull-ups (4 x 8): keep watching for three versions and go for whichever feels like the right resistance for the set + rep structure ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíõ Plate row to extension (3 x 12): pulling through the lats, then extending that lower back and driving the hips through is perfect ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Finished! You strong now üôåü•∞

It‚Äôs a leg day! üíï Back to the weights and getting real strong while keeping it functional! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
This one has a mix of tempos that I promise is going to give the most amazing burn, but once you‚Äôre done your legs will thank you üí™ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
Swipe, save, let‚Äôs gooo üíò ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíï Dumbbell kneeling squat (4 x 12): we‚Äôre driving with the glutes, and keeping the back neutral üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíï Contralateral KB rack lunge (3 x 12 per side): contralateral means we‚Äôre loading the opposite side of the body to the working side, and has been repeatedly shown to significantly change the muscles activated in single-sided movements ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíï Pause squat into jump squat (3 x 8): hold for 3s and then jump as high as you can! The instant change in tempos from one extreme to other will engage your legs so differently to standard constant tempo training üôè ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíï Back squats into pause squats (3 x 6 squats and then 6s hold): this one will burnnnn but you‚Äôll have trained squats through a whole range of movement speeds which has so many benefits for getting more athletic and feeling more badass üí™ ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
üíï Single arm KB swings (4 x 16 total): I show three variations here - the most simple is first, but you can progress onto the second and the third version as you become more and more of a pro üôå ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
And that‚Äôs it! Longer rest periods (90s+) are perfect for this session because the explosive and static movements will be real burners if you‚Äôre not super used to them! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä
